3 Analysis of a variance

3.1 Without Control Variables

one.way <- aov(cohesion_mean ~ exp_condition, data = data)
summary(one.way)
##                Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)  
## exp_condition   1   6.92   6.916   6.519 0.0116 *
## Residuals     167 177.17   1.061                 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

So far the F(1,158) = 8.92, p = .003 is significant.

3.2 With Age and Gender Controlled

one.way <- aov(cohesion_mean ~ exp_condition + age + gender, data = data)
summary(one.way)
##                Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)  
## exp_condition   1   6.92   6.916   6.466 0.0119 *
## age             1   0.20   0.196   0.184 0.6689  
## gender          1   0.48   0.476   0.445 0.5057  
## Residuals     165 176.49   1.070                 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

Neither gender nor age has a significant impact on team cohesion.

So far the F(1,156) = 8.84, p = .003 is significant.

3.3 ANOVA Model Diagnostic

3.3.1 1. linearity assumption of predictors

plot(one.way, 1)

3.3.2 2. Normalverteilung der Residuen

car::qqPlot(one.way)

## [1]   1 144
studentized.residuals <- rstudent(one.way)
car::densityPlot(studentized.residuals) # Dichtekurve der Residuen
# df <- n − k − 1
df <- one.way$df.residual
curve(dt(x, df= df), # theor. Kurve zum Vergleich
      add= TRUE, lwd= 2, lty= 2
) # graph. Parameter

3.3.3 3. Outliers & leverage points

plot(one.way, 5)

car::Boxplot(hatvalues(one.way), id= list(n=1)) # Hebelwerte

## [1] 1
car::outlierTest(one.way)
##    rstudent unadjusted p-value Bonferroni p
## 1 -4.083846         6.9103e-05     0.011678

Invdividual 1 seams to be an outlier.

3.3.4 4. Homoscedacity

## Residuals vs Fitted Plot to observe homoscedacity
plot(one.way, which = 1)

3.3.5 5. multicollinearity

# "discovering statistics using R" p. 293
# If the largest VIF is greater than 10 then there is cause for concern (Bowerman & O'Connell, 1990; Myers, 1990).
car::vif(one.way)
## exp_condition           age        gender 
##      1.005850      1.002838      1.005819
